				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Maligar disappearance warning<a name="16277"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 20 04 8:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I did the turn in to spawn the Maligar Dopplganger the other day when I ran into a problem.  I was kiting him around quite easily until he hit 10% health and disappeared on me.  I still had him on target but he was no where to be found on track.  I had a GM come check it out.  She said he wasn't up anymore, but she would have my note refunded.  I wasn't too bummed he was pretty easy so I started back to Qeynos Hills when who did I find at the zone line??? Maligar's Enraged Dopplganger at 13% health.  Took his head and that was the end of it.
<br />

<br />
I had read a few posts on mobs teleporting accross the zone when they hit 10%, but hadn't experienced it first hand until that day.  So, just a warning for anyone trying out Maligar.  If he disappears on you, check the Qeynos zone line  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
