				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Maligar disappearance warning<a name="21404"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 04 2:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This bug kicks in at the moment the mob turns to flee.
<br />

<br />
It can happen to any mob in any zone. The people who notice it the most are the ones that fear-kite or charm kite. Being inside melee range seems to reduce the chances of =poof=.
<br />

<br />
All the mobs that =poof= go to the same spot in the zone. For instance, a =poof= rhino in OT will go to the exact same location as a =poof= Dragoon in OT. Once you learn the location, you simply have to go over there to finish off poofers. It's almost always up on a wall midway between zonelines.
<br />

<br />
This is NOT a &quot;gate&quot; nor a shadow-step. It is a bug. Aggro is broken once a mob =poofs=.
<br />

<br />
I've heard tell of clever low level groups that camp the =poof= areas finishing off poofers for their loot &amp; full exp from broken charms.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I notice it most commonly on non-social fleeing mobs. I can make a Sarnak Berserker =poof= 100% of the time in OT on Quellious server by simply chant-kiting it until it turns to flee.
<br />

<br />
I've bugged it just about every time it happens (for all the good it's doing).
<br />

<br />
The occurences have reduced quite a bit lately, but I had a mob in Fear =poof= last Saturday (2/7/4) and I had my usual once-a-session Ravenous Nightstalker =poof= in PoN last night (2/13/4).
<br />

<br />
I usually just ignore it and go about my business. I have only been trained by a returning =poof= ONCE in hundreds of =poofs= and I'm fairly certain that was just a coincidence or an odd set of circumstances (I know it was my poofer though because it was the only one of it's type I had left alive in the zone and no spawns were popping anytime soon).
<br />

<br />
-Savidge</span></td>
